Description: Fragment of handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine, micaceous, orange-red; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1373)
